.Dd 2026-07-20
.Dt BEDSTATUS 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm bedstatus
.Nd X11 status bar daemon for
.Xr dwm 1 ,
driven by a periodic root-window-name update
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is the status bar daemon for the author's
.Xr dwm 1 Ns -based
desktop.
Once a second it samples the system, formats a one-line status string, and
publishes it as the X root window's
.Dv WM_NAME
via
.Xr XStoreName 3 .
.Xr dwm 1
reads that property and renders it in its bar.
.Pp
The status line is a concatenation of bracketed sections:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
\&[cpu] [ram] [bat] [wt] [tmr] [net] [vpn] [mic] TIME
.Ed
.Pp
Each section is omitted if its backing data is unavailable
(e.g.\& no battery on a desktop, no lock file from
.Xr wt 1 ,
no timer running).
.Ss Sections
.Bl -tag -width "bat" -compact
.It Sy cpu
CPU usage percent, average frequency, and temperature:
.Li "[<icon> N% (XXXX MHz / NN\(deC)]" .
.It Sy ram
Used memory in IEC units:
.Li "[<icon> N.NN G]" .
.It Sy bat
Battery percentage with icon chosen by charge level (empty/low/half/high/full),
or the charging icon when AC is connected.
Remaining runtime and current power draw are appended in parentheses:
.Li "[<icon> N% (NNm/N.NNW)]" .
Below 10% the icon blinks; below 20% it is shown in the urgent color; below 30%
in the warning color.
.It Sy wt
Active
.Xr wt 1
session, rendered as
.Li "[<stopwatch-icon> stem]"
using the stem stored in the lock file
(see
.Sx FILES ) .
Present only while a session is running.
.It Sy tmr
Countdown to the absolute Unix timestamp stored in the timer file
(see
.Sx FILES ) .
Renders
.Li "[<hourglass-icon> Nunit]"
with units
.Li d Ns / Ns Li h Ns / Ns Li m Ns / Ns Li s .
Within the last 30 seconds the icon blinks, under 60 seconds it is urgent,
under 120 seconds it is a warning.
When the timer has elapsed, the section cycles through the letters of
.Qq ELAPSED
once per second.
.It Sy net
Ethernet and WiFi glyphs (when the corresponding interfaces exist).
A connected interface is plain; an interface with carrier but no default route
(isolated) is shown in the urgent color.
.It Sy vpn
Shield glyph.
Plain when the VPN gateway is reachable, warning when configured but
unreachable, urgent when no VPN interface exists at all.
.It Sy mic
Microphone indicator.
The unmuted state is shown in the urgent color (to draw attention to a hot
microphone); the muted state is plain.
The mute state is queried via
.Xr audioctl 1 .
.It Sy time
Formatted with
.Li "%a %F %T" .
.El
.Sh COLOR CODES
.Nm
embeds single-byte sentinels in the string it publishes.
These are interpreted by this repository's
.Xr dwm 1
build (a
.Qq statuscolors Ns -style
patch) as switches between the user-defined color sets:
.Bl -tag -width "\\ex04" -compact
.It Li \ex01
.Pq Dv COLOR_NORMAL
reset to the bar's default colors.
.It Li \ex03
.Pq Dv COLOR_WARN
use the warning color set (typically yellow).
.It Li \ex04
.Pq Dv COLOR_URGENT
use the urgent color set (typically red); the bar background also flashes
between warning and urgent once per second when this is the active color.
.El
.Pp
Every colored section is followed by a
.Li \ex01
reset.
A stock
.Xr dwm 1
without color support will render the sentinels as nothing (they are
non-printable control characters) and the text will appear uncolored.
.Sh SIGNALS
.Bl -tag -width "SIGUSR1" -compact
.It Dv SIGUSR1
Reset the timer-file cache
.Pq set Li timer_ttl No to 0
and force the next iteration to re-read the timer file.
The signal also interrupts the inter-iteration
.Xr sleep 3 ,
so the refresh happens immediately.
.It Dv SIGINT , Dv SIGTERM
Default disposition (terminate).
.El
.Pp
Both
.Nm
helpers and other tools (the
.Sx timer
helper script below, and
.Xr wt 1
after writing its lock file) signal
.Nm
with
.Dv SIGUSR1
to request a refresh.
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Bl -tag -width "XDG_RUNTIME_DIR" -compact
.It Ev DISPLAY
Selects the X server
.Pq defaults to Li :0 No via Xlib .
.It Ev XDG_RUNTIME_DIR
Location of the timer file and the
.Xr wt 1
lock file.
Falls back to
.Pa /tmp
if unset.
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width "$XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/bedstatus-timer" -compact
.It Pa $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/bedstatus-timer
.Pq or Pa /tmp/bedstatus-timer No if Ev XDG_RUNTIME_DIR No is unset
Single line containing an absolute Unix timestamp (seconds since the epoch)
at which the
.Sy tmr
section should fire.
Read by
.Nm
with a cache TTL of 30 iterations; on parse failure the file is re-read
every 15 iterations.
.It Pa $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/wt.active
.Pq or Pa /tmp/wt.active No if Ev XDG_RUNTIME_DIR No is unset
Lock file written by
.Xr wt 1
when a session is running.
Format:
.Li <PID> <stem>
followed by a newline, where
.Ar stem
is the basename of the selected CSV with
.Li .csv
stripped.
Read by
.Nm
every iteration (no caching).
.El
.Sh TIMER HELPER
The
.Pa timer
shell script, installed alongside
.Nm ,
is the canonical writer of the timer file.
It accepts:
.Bl -tag -width "timer -h N" -compact
.It Ic timer Fl s Ar sec
Set the timer for
.Ar sec
seconds.
.It Ic timer Fl m Ar min
Set the timer for
.Ar min
minutes.
.It Ic timer Fl h Ar hr
Set the timer for
.Ar hr
hours.
.It Ic timer Fl a
Add to the existing timer instead of replacing it.
May be combined with
.Fl s Ns / Ns Fl m Ns / Ns Fl h Ns / Ns Fl a .
.It Ic timer Fl r
Remove the timer file.
.It Ic timer
.Pq no arguments
Print the current timer file contents.
.El
.Pp
After any modification
.Pa timer
runs
.Li pkill -USR1 bedstatus
to request an immediate refresh.
.Sh EXAMPLES
Start from
.Pa ~/.xsession :
.Bd -literal -offset indent
bedstatus &
.Ed
.Pp
Set a 5-minute kitchen timer:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ timer -m 5
.Ed
.Pp
Add another 30 seconds:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ timer -a -s 30
.Ed
.Pp
Clear it:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ timer -r
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr wt 1 ,
.Xr audioctl 1 ,
.Xr dwm 1 ,
.Xr XStoreName 3 ,
.Xr sndioctl 1 ,
.Xr wpctl 1
.Sh BUGS
The VPN detection is hard-coded via
.Dv VPN_GATEWAY
(currently
.Li 192.168.64.1 )
and
.Dv VPN_IFACE
(currently
.Li wg0 )
in
.Pa bedstatus.h .
These are site-specific; on any other setup the
.Sy vpn
section should be recompiled or the constants edited.
.Pp
The
.Sy mic
section silently disappears when
.Xr audioctl 1
is not on
.Ev PATH
or returns nothing (e.g.\& on FreeBSD, where the wrapper has no dispatch).
.Pp
All glyphs are private-use Font Awesome code points in the U+F000 range; a
Font Awesome installation is required for them to render \(em otherwise the
icons appear as blank boxes.
.Pp
The timer file is read with a 30-second cache, so a very short timer set
externally may briefly show a stale value until the next refresh signal
arrives.
